    <question>
        <prompt>The Harlem Renaissance was significant because it:</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Promoted racial segregation</option>
            <option letter="b">Celebrated African American cultural achievement</option>
            <option letter="c">Focused only on political reform</option>
            <option letter="d">Supported economic policies</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>The Harlem Renaissance was significant for celebrating African American cultural achievement through literature, music, art, and intellectual discourse. This cultural movement helped establish African American art forms as integral parts of American culture, challenged racial stereotypes, and fostered pride in African American identity and heritage while influencing broader American cultural expressions.</explanation>
